{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Getting its inspiration from how humans perceive the environment by distinguishing scenes through semantic objects and their topological relations, SGPR utilizes semantic segmentation on raw 3D point clouds to obtain instances and further collects semantic and topological information together to acquire nodes forming the semantic graph.",
    "It leverages the semantic level to achieve superior robustness to environmental changes.",
    "The method is rotation invariant since the network can capture topological and semantic information from the point cloud.",
    "However, given its reliance on semantic segmentation, SGPR still suffers from bottlenecks, such as the test dataset's pre-defined semantic classes.",
    "Zhu et al. (2020) proposed GOSMatch, a graph-of-semantics matching method for loop detection and 3D-PCPR."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Zhu et al. (2020) proposed GOSMatch, a graph-of-semantics matching method for loop detection and 3D-PCPR."
  ]
}